---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { APP_URL, t } from '../../i18n/ui';

const tr = t('en');
---

<Base
  lang="en"
  routeKey="pricing"
  title="Pricing — Sereno is free"
  description="Sereno is free: local mode costs nothing to run, and the free cloud account is sustainable without ads or selling data. Here's how."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="eyebrow">Pricing</span>
        <h1>Free. And here's why that's not suspicious.</h1>
        <p>
          A free app deserves an honest explanation — especially an app about
          money.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="plans">
        <div class="plan card">
          <h2>On your device</h2>
          <p class="price"><span class="amount">€0</span></p>
          <p class="plan-note">No account, no setup</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Transactions, budgets, statistics, calendar</li>
            <li>Strata, recurring rules, installments, templates</li>
            <li>100% local: your data never leaves your device</li>
            <li>Installable, works offline</li>
            <li>CSV export and full backup</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href={APP_URL} aria-label={tr('cta.openApp.aria')}>{tr('cta.openApp')}</a>
        </div>

        <div class="plan card">
          <h2>With an account</h2>
          <p class="price"><span class="amount">€0</span></p>
          <p class="plan-note">Optional, when you need it</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Everything in local mode, plus:</li>
            <li>Sync across devices</li>
            <li>Multiple accounts (checking, savings, cash…)</li>
            <li>Custom categories</li>
            <li>Server-side recurring rules, even with the app closed</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={APP_URL}>Create an account from the app</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose why">
        <h2>How is this sustainable?</h2>
        <p>
          Local mode costs literally nothing to run: the app is a static site,
          your data lives with you. The cloud account costs a few cents per
          user — sustainable for an independent project as long as Sereno stays
          lean, with no marketing team to feed.
        </p>
        <p>
          One day a <strong>Sereno+</strong> tier may exist for advanced use,
          and it will be announced here, clearly. Two commitments won't change:
          <strong>never ads</strong>, <strong>never selling data</strong> —
          Sereno's business model cannot be the very thing it's trying to spare
          you from.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 42px);
  }

  .plans {
    display: grid;
    gap: 24px;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .plans {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .plan {
    padding: 32px 28px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .plan h2 {
    font-size: 21px;
  }

  .price {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 44px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 40;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .plan-note {
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .plan ul {
    margin: 12px 0 20px;
    padding-left: 18px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 15px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .plan .btn {
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .why h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
  }
</style>
